@MattWalshBlog If the price of the stock falls to $80 I now "buy" the shares at $80 and I profit $20/share I sold at $100. Think of it as a stock buy in reverse order. So I bought shares at $80 and sold them at $100 just in the reverse order we usually think of.

@MattWalshBlog Example: Say a stock is trading for $100 and I want to sell it short. I "sell" the shares at $100 usually with shares I've borrowed from the brokerage house. I never owned the stock, I just sold some borrowed stock. Now to make money the price must drop.
